  "body_html": "<div>The diagram below shows the metabolism of arachidonic acid:<br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/pdd502b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/pdd502.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/pdd502b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><div class='alert alert-warning'>Leukotrienes<br /><ul><li>LTB4: B4 (before) leukocytes comes LTB4</li><li>the rest A, C, D & E constrict the lungs</li></ul><br />Endoperoxides<br /><ul><li>THROMBOxane think THROMBOSIS: platelets aggregated and vasoconstriction. Prostacyclin is the opposite</li></ul></div></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">2</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">1556</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Physiology</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Basic Cellular Physiology</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\nThe diagram below shows the metabolism of arachidonic acid:<br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/pdd502b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/pdd502.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/pdd502b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><div class='alert alert-warning'>Leukotrienes<br /><ul><li>LTB4: B4 (before) leukocytes comes LTB4</li><li>the rest A, C, D & E constrict the lungs</li></ul><br />Endoperoxides<br /><ul><li>THROMBOxane think THROMBOSIS: platelets aggregated and vasoconstriction. Prostacyclin is the opposite</li></ul></div></div>\n\n\n<BR><BR><br><br></div>",
